-- South Korea Builders May Win $2 Billion Saudi Refinery Orders, Daily Says
-- Jungmin Hong
-- 2010-07-11T09:23:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/south-korea-builders-may-win-2-billion-saudi-refinery-orders-daily-says.html

          
          
             South Korean builders Daelim
Industrial Co. and SK Engineering & Construction Co. may win
refinery orders in Saudi Arabia worth a combined $2.2 billion,
the Seoul Economic Daily reported today, citing an official at a
South Korean builder. Saudi Arabian Oil Co. will announce the
bidding results later this month, according to the Korean-
language report.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
